<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-661-065  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 661 065.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Vision Graphics andamp; Image Processing  Dec 1990 v52 n3p416(21).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Index-based object recognition in pictorial data management.andO;(technical)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Grosky, William I.; Mehrotra, Rajiv.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>A methodology for the recognition of two-dimensional object shapecombines a new data-driven indexing approach with the standardmodel-driven approach.andP;  There is a growing interest in multimedia,object-oriented data base management systems (DBMSs) that canstore images as well as text.andP;  A central problem of such systemsis the implementation of a viable strategy for querying data thatis in both object and text forms.andP;  An image DBMS technology isdeveloped that employs model-based representation of images bytheir content.andP;  A querying process is implemented for efficientrecognition of object models (images): data-driven indexedhypotheses (DDIH).andP;  The technique constructs indexes to sets ofmodels from all of their noise-insensitive features which areefficiently organized as a feature index tree.andP;  Experimentsdemonstrate the viability of the DDIH method.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Data Base Management SystemsObject-Oriented Data BasesObject RecognitionIndexed FilesNew TechniqueQuery ProcessingImage EncodingShape.andO;Feature:   illustrationcharttable.andO;Caption:   The data-driven indexed hypotheses paradigm. (chart)Feature index tree with distortion sensitivity of 0. (chart)Average performance using the index trees. (table)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>